Speaking at Wisconsin tool company, president pledges to take ‘sledgehammer’ to regulations as he signs measure cracking down on H-1B scheme

Donald Trump promised to take a “sledgehammer” to what he considered job-killing regulations as he signed an executive order to crack down on fraud and abuse in foreign worker programmes.

Hitting a familiar note on economic populism, the US president visited a tool manufacturing company in Kenosha, Wisconsin
